.TH LORD 1 "June 2026" "exec" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lord \- run Codex with local AGENTS instructions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY lord
.RI [ option | @option ]...
.RI [ prompt ...]
.YS
.SY lord
.RI [ option | @option ]...
.RI [ prompt ...]
<
.I input
.YS
.SY pray
.RI [ pattern ]
.YS
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lord
is a small wrapper around
.BR "codex exec" .
It chooses an AGENTS profile when needed, adds a few Codex flags, runs the
prompt through Codex, and caches captured stdout.
.PP
If
.I ./AGENTS.md
exists,
.B lord
uses it as-is.  In that case no internal profile is installed and the file is
not overwritten.
.PP
If
.I ./AGENTS.md
does not exist,
.B lord
temporarily links one internal profile into the current directory for the
Codex run, then removes that link on exit.
.PP
The default profile is
.B repo
inside a Git worktree or any of its subdirectories.  Outside a Git worktree the
default profile is
.BR unix-command .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Print help and exit.
.TP
.BR -v ", " --verbose
Print verbose wrapper behavior to stderr and run Codex without capturing
stdout.
.TP
.BR -f ", " --force ", " --dont-panic
Pass
.B --dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox
through to
.BR "codex exec" .
.TP
.BR --fast ", " --quick ", " @fast ", " @quick
Request low Codex reasoning effort.
.TP
.BR --accurate ", " --careful ", " @accurate ", " @careful
Request high Codex reasoning effort.
.TP
.BR --very-careful ", " --xhigh ", " @very-careful ", " @xhigh
Request extra-high Codex reasoning effort.
.TP
.BR --effort " " LEVEL ", " --thinking " " LEVEL ", " --effort= LEVEL ", " --thinking= LEVEL
.TQ
.BR @effort= LEVEL ", " @thinking= LEVEL
Set Codex reasoning effort explicitly.
.I LEVEL
must be
.BR low ,
.BR medium ,
.BR high ,
or
.BR xhigh .
.TP
.B @echo
Print the
.B codex exec
command that would be run instead of running it.
.TP
.B @yhwh
Pass
.B --skip-git-repo-check
to Codex and do not use an AGENTS file.
.TP
.B @no-agents
Do not use an AGENTS file.
.TP
.BR @profile= PROFILE ", " @agents= PROFILE ", " @pray= PROFILE
Select an internal AGENTS profile.
Known aliases include
.BR unix ,
.BR command ,
.BR unix-command ,
.BR repo ,
.BR git ,
.BR code ,
.BR bible ,
.BR nameless ,
and
.BR we-the-nameless .
Aliases are matched against Markdown files in
.IR $EXEC/etc/lord .
.TP
.BI @ flag
Pass
.BI -- flag
through to
.BR "codex exec" .
.TP
.B --
Stop wrapper option parsing.  Remaining arguments become part of the prompt.
.SH PROFILE SELECTION
.TP
.B unix-command
Uses
.IR $EXEC/etc/lord/AGENTS-unix-command.md .
This profile makes
.B lord
act like a terse Unix filter: transform input and print only the requested
output.
.TP
.B repo
Uses
.IR $EXEC/etc/lord/AGENTS-code.md .
The aliases
.BR git
and
.B code
select the same profile.
.TP
.B bible
Uses
.IR $EXEC/etc/lord/AGENTS-bible.md .
The aliases
.BR nameless
and
.B we-the-nameless
select the same profile.
.PP
Profile matching is implemented by matching the selected profile string against
the basename or full path of files under
.IR $EXEC/etc/lord .
The match must select exactly one file.
.SH GIT HANDLING
Inside a Git worktree,
.B lord
runs
.B codex exec
normally.
.PP
Outside a Git worktree,
.B lord
passes
.B --skip-git-repo-check
and
.B "-s workspace-write"
to Codex.
.SH INPUT HANDLING
.B lord
does not pre-process stdin.  Stdin is inherited by
.BR "codex exec" .
Command-line arguments that are not wrapper options are joined with spaces to
form the Codex prompt.
.SH OUTPUT AND CACHE
Without
.B --verbose
or
.BR @echo ,
.B lord
captures Codex stdout, prints it, and writes a copy to
.I $HOME/.cache/lord
using a timestamped filename.
.PP
If Codex exits non-zero,
.B lord
prints Codex stderr and returns the failing status.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B EXEC
Root of the exec checkout.  If unset,
.B lord
derives it from the location of the script.
.TP
.B LORD_PROFILE
Default profile name.  Command-line profile selectors override it.
.TP
.B HOME
Used for the output cache.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ./AGENTS.md
Existing local instructions.  If present, this file is used as-is.
.TP
.I $EXEC/bin/lord
The main wrapper.
.TP
.I $EXEC/bin/pray
Profile lookup helper.
.TP
.I $EXEC/etc/lord/AGENTS-*.md
Internal profiles consumed by
.B lord
and
.BR pray .
.TP
.I $HOME/.cache/lord
Timestamped captured outputs.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
echo INPUT | lord "uppercase it"
lord "fix the failing test"
lord @agents=bible "explain the semantic layer before editing"
lord @echo "show me the codex command"
pray unix
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR codex (1),
.BR git (1)
